By James Samuel The State Council of Nigeria Union of Journalists have suspended the chairman of Sports Writers Association, SWAN, Niger State chapter, Abu Hassan. The suspension was contained in a statement jointly signed by the State Chairman and Secretary Comrade Abdul Idris and Abu Nmadu. The statement indicates that the Swan chairman was suspended based on his failure to adhere to the directive of the National Secretary of the Union not to attend the Port Harcourt SWAN faction Congress. The State Council of Nigeria Union of Journalists directed the suspended Chairman of Swan to submit all documents of SWAN in his possession to the State Secretariat of the Union at IBB Pen House, Minna immediately. The statement also warned the suspended Chairman to comply fully with this directive without delay.